    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2002 BMW M3 Coupe featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a factory-calibrated variable M differential lock for optimal torque distribution. This specimen has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral G-loads. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, providing the telepathic feedback and damping characteristics synonymous with the E46 chassis. An uncompromising example for the purist.",
